- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer parameter `diff` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 50.
- The integer result is the number of unique arithmetic triplets in the integer array `nums` with the given difference `diff`.
- Each arithmetic triplet `(i, j, k)` in the result satisfies the conditions `i < j < k`, `nums[j] - nums[i] == diff`, and `nums[k] - nums[j] == diff`.